liblightgrep
------------------------------------------
Lightgrep is a new regular expression engine, designed specifically for digital
forensics.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.6-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  libicu70-70.1-1
  liblightgrep-devel-1.4-1bl4
  liblightgrep0-1.4-1bl4
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/strozfriedberg/liblightgrep

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/strozfriedberg/liblightgrep/archive/refs/tags/v1.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack liblightgrep-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./liblightgrep-1.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblightgrep-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblightgrep-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblightgrep0-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblightgrep-devel-1.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(liblightgrep)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/liblightgrep.README
  /usr/share/doc/liblightgrep/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/liblightgrep/README.md

(liblightgrep0)
  /usr/bin/cyglightgrep-0.dll

(liblightgrep-devel)
  /usr/include/lightgrep/api.h
  /usr/include/lightgrep/encodings.h
  /usr/include/lightgrep/search_hit.h
  /usr/include/lightgrep/transforms.h
  /usr/include/lightgrep/util.h
  /usr/lib/liblightgrep.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/lightgrep.pc

